Zabbix 7.4.x Outlook-friendly HTML Email Templates
Compact severity-color version v26
Server name used in links/footer: zabbix01.example.local

Purpose:
- Outlook-friendly HTML message templates for Zabbix Email media type.
- Trigger templates: Problem, Problem recovery, Problem update.
- Non-trigger templates: Discovery, Autoregistration, Service, Service recovery, Service update, Internal problem, Internal problem recovery.

Current design notes:
- v26 active template code is rolled back to the last good v23 behavior.
- Message width is compact but can expand consistently when long text needs room.
- Action buttons use the v21 bordered-wrapper design so Outlook keeps the bottom border visible without double-width borders in browser previews.
- Footer has three equal visual sections: server link, severity text, linked tags.
- Item/Value table intentionally keeps four rows for now.
- Trigger templates still contain temporary native-template logic around Item/Value rows. This is only a best-effort workaround for Zabbix indexed item macros that may resolve to *UNKNOWN*.

TODO for future Zabbix script media type:
- Replace these native HTML message templates with a Python script media type.
- Build the HTML from these templates as a base.
- Remove all template-side unknown/hiding/substitution logic.
- Query Zabbix/API data directly in Python.
- Render only real item rows.
- Skip non-existing items entirely.
- Deduplicate repeated items by itemid.
- URL-encode tag-search links safely in Python instead of relying on regex substitutions in Zabbix templates.

Severity color mapping used for Problem and Problem update:
- Disaster: soft red
- High: soft pink
- Average: soft orange
- Warning: soft yellow
- Information / Informational / Not classified / others: soft blue

Recovery templates:
- Main header and issue header: soft green
- Text: ✔ Problem resolved
- Previous severity badge: still colored by original severity

Version history:
v4:
- Fixed Outlook class handling by using exactly one severity class on colored elements:
  sevBlock{TRIGGER.SEVERITY}, sevBadge{TRIGGER.SEVERITY}.

v5:
- Removed redundant top status/header band from Problem, Problem recovery, and Problem update.
- Renamed action links to Graph / Item / Trigger / Event.
- Styled Item, Trigger, and Event like the Graph button.

v6:
- Removed Event ID detail rows where the Event action button already exists.
- Recolored trigger titles and action buttons by severity/recovery hue.
- Added right-side status icons in the issue header.

v7:
- Restored native warning/check icon coloring behavior.
- Rebuilt Graph / Item / Trigger / Event as Outlook-friendly table-cell buttons.
- Reduced left/right content padding from 16px to 8px.

v8:
- Updated Problem, Problem recovery, and Problem update action buttons for Zabbix 7.4+ HTTPS routes.
- Added the direct chart-image button using the framed-picture Unicode symbol.
- Replaced trigger footers with the three-part footer.

v10:
- Reordered action buttons to: image, Graph, Item, Trigger, Event.
- Rebuilt trigger footers as equal-width sections with subtle dot separators.
- Added #tag rendering with macro functions where tag names/values are URL-safe.

v11:
- Made zabbix01.example.local in the footer a link to https://zabbix01.example.local/ while preserving footer styling.
- Removed # from the footer severity text.
- Converted trigger footer tags into same-style search links where tag names/values are URL-safe.

v12:
- Suppressed footer tag entries matching Application: Interface ...
- Trimmed the space after tag colon for generated tag-search URL values.

v13:
- Routed Application:* tag links to the Items search page and other tags to the Triggers search page.
- Rebuilt Item values as a two-column Item / Value table.
- Added first attempt at unknown item-row handling.

v14:
- Kept the item table inside the message width with fixed table layout and wrapping.
- Removed the separate “Item values” title above the table.

v15:
- Made the Item/Value table more compact.

v16:
- Reduced overall template width and aligned header, details table, item table, action row, and footer to the same compact width.
- Changed Item/Value table to fill the compact content width.

v17:
- Allowed compact 520px message width to expand consistently up to 676px for long text.
- Relaxed forced wrapping so text uses available width before wrapping.

v18:
- Removed Operational data rows from trigger templates.
- Footer severity text changed from “Severity: X” to “Severity X”.
- Added another attempt to hide unknown rows.

v19:
- Attempted to prevent Outlook button bottom-border loss with a table-level bottom border.
- Superseded because it could create double-width borders.

v20:
- Attempted to prevent Outlook button bottom-border loss with a dedicated 1px row.
- Superseded because it rendered incorrectly in browser previews.

v21:
- Replaced v19/v20 border approaches with a single bordered wrapper cell around the action buttons.
- This kept one clean visible border in browser previews and fixed the Outlook missing-bottom-border issue.

v23:
- Removed severity from the colored header meta line to avoid duplication.
- Problem update header now says Status: PROBLEM UPDATE and keeps Age.
- Renamed Event time rows to Problem started.
- Renamed Update time to Last update in update notifications.
- Kept four Item/Value rows using the last accepted v23 native-template behavior.

v24:
- Attempted visible-text blanking for unknown Item/Value rows.
- Reverted later because real Zabbix messages still showed unwanted output.

v25:
- Attempted light-gray None markers and macro syntax changes for unknown Item/Value rows.
- Reverted because real Zabbix messages rendered worse than v23.

v26:
- Rolled active template code back to the last good v23 behavior.
- Added a version/purpose HTML comment near the top of every message template.
- Cleaned and ordered this version-history block.
- Added the future Python script media type TODO notes above.

Paste each Message body into the matching message template in:
Alerts -> Media types -> Email -> Message templates
Make sure Email media type uses Message format: HTML.


